<h2 style="text-align: center">TRADITIONAL AGRICULTURE IN INDIA</h2>

<p>Traditional farming is where the farmer has a mixed farm of livestock and crops. The farmer uses manure from the livestock to fertilize the crops and some of the crop to feed the livestock. Farmers of this type operate with the minimum of supplies purchased from outside the farm.
<p>Traditional Indian agricultural systems can be classified into one or more of the following basic categories.
<p style="margin-left: 150px;">&#8226 Shifting Cultivation
<br>&#8226 Nomadic Pastoralism
<br>&#8226 Continuous Cultivation
<br>&#8226 Mixed Subsistence Farming

<p>Irrigation systems: - 
<p>Traditional Irrigation systems in India include: -
<p style="margin-left: 150px;">&#8226 <u>Moat</u>: - 
<br>Moat irrigation system is a manual type of irrigation in which the water is drawn from a well and the plants are irrigated.
<br>&#8226 <u>Chain pump</u>: - 
<br>A chain pump consists of two large wheels, connected by a chain. Buckets are hanged on the chain. The bottom wheel is half immersed in the water source. As the wheel is turned, the buckets dip into the pool and pick up water. The chain then lifts them to the upper wheel, where the water from the buckets is transferred to the pool. The chain then carries the empty buckets back down to be refilled and the process continues.

\image image1
<br>Fig. 1. Chain pump irrigation
<p style="text-align: right">(http://www.personal.psu.edu/amp5364/HangingGardens.html)

<p style="margin-left: 150px;">&#8226 <u>Dhekli</u>: - 
<br>Dhekli is a traditional system of irrigation used in rural regions. In this system, man or woman uses rope and container to obtain water from well for irrigation purpose.
<br>&#8226 <u>Rahat</u>: - 
<br>Rahat is a traditional method of irrigation in which animals like oxen are used to pull out water from the wells. This water is then evenly spread out over the fields. It is cheap but not very efficient method of irrigation.
<p style="text-align: right">(http://www.meritnation.com/discuss/question/2409081)

\image image2
<br>Fig. 2. Rahat irrigation
<p style="text-align: right">(http://demo.mastermindtutor.com/class-8/biology/chapter1/note3.htm)

<p>There are two major types of irrigation systems.
